snippet: The impact of the death of Lt. Gen. Hussein Ayoub Ishaq was unclear, an expert said, because successors usually await and rebel forces have no aircraft.
abstract: Lt Gen Hussein Ayoub Ishaq, general in charge of Syria's air defense, is killed in fighting near Damascus; it is unclear what effect Ishaq's death will have on conflict.

byline.original: By ANNE BARNARD and BEN HUBBARD
byline.contributor: Mohammad Ghannam contributed reporting from Beirut, Karam Shoumali from Istanbul, and an employee of The New York Times from Damascus, Syria.

lead_paragraph: The impact of the death of Lt. Gen. Hussein Ayoub Ishaq was unclear, an expert said, because successors usually await and rebel forces have no aircraft.

headline.main: Chief of Syria’s Air Defense Dies in Battle Near Capital
